whichever team\", \"from\": 1215, \"to\": 1229}, {\"ngram\": \"the FIBA Olympic Qualifying Tournament\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1273}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first opponent on the schedule is Team Germany, last summer\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s World Cup champions, on July 27 followed by France (July 30) and the winner of the Olympic Qualifying Tournament (Aug. 2).\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1539, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1387, \"end\": 1399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999967103577, \"rank\": 3.2876205333427712e-09, \"text\": \"Team Germany\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1461, \"end\": 1467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999607097326535, \"rank\": 3.927863624604519e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The first opponent\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1367}, {\"ngram\": \"the schedule\", \"from\": 1371, \"to\": 1383}, {\"ngram\": \"last summer\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s World Cup champions\", \"from\": 1401, \"to\": 1436}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 1441, \"to\": 1445}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 1469, \"to\": 1473}, {\"ngram\": \"the winner\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1492}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Qualifying Tournament\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1529}, {\"ngram\": \"Aug.\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1535}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hachimura is likely to play in his second Olympic Games just months removed from the best statistical season of his NBA career.\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1668, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1541, \"end\": 1550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hachimura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\"}, {\"begin\": 1657, \"end\": 1660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.026069157397085e-29, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his second Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1572, \"to\": 1596}, {\"ngram\": \"the best statistical season\", \"from\": 1622, \"to\": 1649}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 6-foot-8 forward averaged 13.6 points (most since 2020-21) while shooting 53.7% from the field (career-best) and 42.2% from 3-point range (on 3.4 attempts per game, both career-highs) in 68 games played, including 39 starts.\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1897, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"13.6 points\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1710}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 1758, \"to\": 1767}, {\"ngram\": \"3-point range\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 1810}, {\"ngram\": \"3.4 attempts\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 1827}, {\"ngram\": \"game\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 1836}, {\"ngram\": \"68 games\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 1868}, {\"ngram\": \"39 starts\", \"from\": 1887, \"to\": 1896}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Lakers went 22-10 to end the regular season with Hachimura in the starting lineup, as he averaged 15.9 points and 5.1 rebounds while shooting 57.6% from the floor and 44.4% from downtown in that span.\", \"from\": 1898, \"to\": 2102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1951, \"end\": 1960, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rui_Hachimura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hachimura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\"